content.description:
PIGS IN HEAVEN 5.4 ** 80 F (6b)

Begin at the lowest point on the cliff (far left end) behind the large boulder. Follow the bolts up and right to the 2 cold shut anchors just below the top. Very nice, consistent climbing.
content.location: At the left end of the Flying Pig Wall (shaded formation right of the main Turtle Island area)

content.description:
NO-NEE 5.5 ** 75 M (3b)

Begin at the far right end of the cliff and climb to the chain anchors. Needs an assortment of cams or nuts to protect.
content.protection: Mixed 3 bolts and a range of cams or nuts.
content.location: Begin at the far right end of the cliff and climb to the chain anchors.

content.description:
IN-FLEW-ENZA 5.6 * 75 M (4b)

Begin about 20 right of PIGS IN HEAVEN and climb up to share the cold shut anchors. Needs an assortment of cams or nuts to protect.
content.protection: Mixed, 4 bolts and an assortment of cams
content.location: Begin about 20 right of PIGS IN HEAVEN

content.description:
HO-NEE 5.4 ** 85 M (4b)

Begin at the low point of the right side of the cliff (just behind the pine tree) and climb up and diagonally right to the chain anchors above the top ledge. Very nice climbing, needs an assortment of cams or nuts to protect.
content.protection: Mixed 4 bolts plus an assortment of cams or nuts
content.location: Begin at the low point of the right side of the cliff (just behind the pine tree) and climb up and diagonally right to the chain anchors above the top ledge.
